Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.02,0:02:00.70,Bengoshi-110_Sign2,Sign bottom,0,0,0,,{\3c&H616B87&}Call 110 immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.12,0:01:59.82,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I'm not suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.53,0:02:12.02,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:12.83,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.83,0:02:16.29,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Look, I sewed these today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.29,0:02:18.43,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Misshapen somewhat, but not bad, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.65,0:02:20.55,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.65,0:02:20.91,Bengoshi-Divorce_Claim1,Top of letter,0,0,0,,Petition to Divorce
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.91,0:02:22.32,Bengoshi-Divorce_Claim2,Zoom of letter,0,0,0,,Petition to Divorce
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.91,0:02:22.32,Bengoshi-Divorce_Names,Name,0,0,0,,Sakagami Takeshi    Sakagami Izumi
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.68,0:02:23.62,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.62,0:02:25.32,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Let's get divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.35,0:02:27.81,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,What's with this, all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.81,0:02:29.72,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Do you know what day it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.72,0:02:32.55,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,It's the day you got fired \Nfrom your last job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.55,0:02:36.84,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I told you that I'd divorce you if you \Ncouldn't find employment in a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:38.10,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Hang on a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.10,0:02:39.53,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Your name goes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.53,0:02:40.50,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Press your seal here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.50,0:02:43.04,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,But, I'm going to job interviews.\N I'm making an effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.04,0:02:44.90,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I tell my subordinates daily
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.90,0:02:48.29,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,that their efforts are meaningless \Nif they don't produce results.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.29,0:02:50.36,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,What'll happen if we got divorced?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.36,0:02:54.54,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,The kids are still little. \NThey need a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.54,0:02:58.72,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Sorry to say, but the kids \Nalready have a new Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.13,0:02:59.76,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.76,0:03:01.85,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,He's the president of a partner company.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.85,0:03:04.11,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,He's got money, he's reliable,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.11,0:03:06.25,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,and he'd be far better for the kids
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.25,0:03:09.44,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,than a loser father like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.44,0:03:10.76,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,You were cheating on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.76,0:03:13.27,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,It's because you're spineless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.27,0:03:16.59,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,That's enough to make\N you cheat on me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.59,0:03:17.93,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Don't talk so loudly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.93,0:03:20.27,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Just press your seal here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.27,0:03:30.11,Bengoshi-Divorce_Claim2,Zoom of letter,0,0,0,,Children in wife's custody: {\c&H21302D&}Ikegami Daichi, Ikegami Yuna, Ikegami Sorata
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.34,0:03:34.82,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,You're taking the children \Naway from me, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.82,0:03:38.02,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Of course. I'm their mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.02,0:03:40.73,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Or do you think an unemployed,\N inadequate man like you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.73,0:03:43.49,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,could care for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.49,0:03:51.69,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Papa, I have to pee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.69,0:03:54.20,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Mama will take you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.20,0:03:55.58,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.27,0:03:57.85,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.15,0:04:10.69,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,Rock paper scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.69,0:04:11.76,Default,Sorata,0,0,0,,I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.76,0:04:12.46,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,You lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:16.96,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,Rock paper scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.79,0:04:22.32,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.77,0:04:27.11,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,You again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.11,0:04:29.09,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun talked to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.09,0:04:32.42,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,He said, "Papa does all \Nthe household chores,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.42,0:04:34.89,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,and takes care of the three of us."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.52,0:04:37.45,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You're a homemaker husband, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.97,0:04:39.62,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Something wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.62,0:04:42.83,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,No, no. Nothing wrong at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.83,0:04:47.77,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun bragged that \Nhis Papa is always home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.63,0:04:51.09,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:55.96,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,my life with my children \Nmight be coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.04,0:05:01.38,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I know I'm overstepping \Nmy bounds, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.21,0:05:03.91,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,are you getting a divorce?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.01,0:05:09.94,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,It's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:12.88,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I couldn't find \Nemployment for a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.88,0:05:15.98,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,and my wife was the breadwinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.01,0:05:20.21,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,But to be honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.21,0:05:24.19,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I don't want to leave my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:43.31,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Why am I telling{\i1} you{\i0} all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.61,0:05:47.55,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,It's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.55,0:05:52.43,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,that the mother has the advantage \Nwhen it comes to custody battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.22,0:05:55.73,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Even more so when\Nthe children are young.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.73,0:05:59.64,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,However, if you believe a father \Ncan never be awarded custody,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.64,0:06:00.73,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,that is not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.73,0:06:02.36,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:06.12,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,With regard to marriage laws, \Nmen and women are treated equally.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.52,0:06:10.37,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You've been unable to \Nfind work for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.37,0:06:11.89,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,However, you supported your family
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:14.39,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,by doing chores and looking \Nafter your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.39,0:06:18.37,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I believe you have a good \Nchance of receiving custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.37,0:06:19.86,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:23.72,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,A laid-off father can get custody?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.72,0:06:26.09,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I don't believe it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.09,0:06:27.61,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Like I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.61,0:06:30.78,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,men and women are equal under the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.78,0:06:32.11,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,In your household,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.11,0:06:34.94,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,the mother earns the money \Nto support the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.94,0:06:38.50,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,In which case you can get \Nchild support from her,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:40.47,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,and you raise your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.84,0:06:43.03,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Is that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.03,0:06:44.09,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.80,0:06:49.56,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,If we can prove that the children \Nwould be happier living with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.56,0:06:51.29,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,"Prove"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.19,0:06:54.70,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.99,0:06:58.49,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:00.58,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.82,0:07:03.62,Bengoshi-Divorce_Claim2,Zoom of letter,0,0,0,,{\3c&HA7A6B6&}Petition to Divorce
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.66,0:07:14.76,Bengoshi-Title,,0,0,0,,Divorce Chaser\N{\fs25}~Let's Turn Your Tears into Money~
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.10,0:07:19.94,Bengoshi-Ep_Title,Left caption,0,0,0,,Divorce Chaser Episode 8 \NWhat Happens to the Children's Future? A Messy Custody Battle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:23.74,Bengoshi-Divorce_Notes,Letter top,0,0,0,,Sakagami Takeshi (42) \NFired from an electrical company a year ago,\N and became a homemaker husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:23.74,Bengoshi-Divorce_Notes,Letter bottom,0,0,0,,{\a11}Wife: Sakagami Izumi (38)\N Interior decorator company \Nmanagerial assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.58,0:07:21.89,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.89,0:07:23.75,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Sakagami Takeshi, 42 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.74,0:07:26.94,Bengoshi-Credits_Takeshi,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}This episode's client:\N Sakagami Takeshi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.75,0:07:27.08,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Fired from an electrical \Ncompany a year ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.08,0:07:28.71,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,and became a homemaker husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.08,0:07:28.71,Bengoshi-Divorce_Notes,Letter,0,0,0,,{\a2}{\fs30}{\b1}Homemaker Husband{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.71,0:07:31.52,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Wife, Sakagami Izumi, 38 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:32.45,Bengoshi-Credits_Yoshie,Caption left,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Office landlord: \NToyama Yoshie
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:32.45,Bengoshi-Credits_Rina,Caption right,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Temp:\N Shinozuka Rina
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.52,0:07:33.76,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Interior decorator company \Nmanagerial assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.76,0:07:37.23,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,So the male-female roles \Nreversed after you were fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.23,0:07:39.29,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Um... and you two are?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.29,0:07:40.24,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,I'm a temp.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.24,0:07:41.02,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,I'm the landlord.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.02,0:07:41.93,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Landlord?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.93,0:07:46.19,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Everyone, please mind your own business,\N and get back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.19,0:07:48.00,Default,BotHakamada,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.00,0:07:50.33,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,What's the reason for the divorce?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.33,0:07:53.90,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm Sensei's assistant, Nonomura.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.90,0:07:55.13,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.63,0:07:57.51,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,The reason for the divorce is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.51,0:07:59.35,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,That's an easy one!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.35,0:08:03.01,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,The wife got fed up with her \Njobless, pathetic husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.01,0:08:05.11,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,and stuck him with a Petition to Divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.11,0:08:07.98,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,She jumped ship in \Nfavor of a capable man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.98,0:08:09.08,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,You're being too blunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.08,0:08:11.36,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Please get back to your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.83,0:08:13.72,Default,BotHakamada,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.93,0:08:16.24,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Please excuse them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.24,0:08:17.71,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.71,0:08:19.76,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,What they said is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:24.71,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I had been warned by my wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.71,0:08:27.65,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,that if I didn't find employment \Nwithin a year after getting fired,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.65,0:08:30.66,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,she would divorce me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.66,0:08:32.61,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I thought she was kidding,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:34.84,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,but I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:34.84,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Hakamada's Assistant:\N Nonomura Kanae
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:38.21,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,She said she's going to remarry
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.21,0:08:42.22,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,the president of an associate company\N as soon as the divorce is official.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.22,0:08:44.52,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,That is an intelligent choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.52,0:08:48.53,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,A hopeful company president \Nis better than a hopeless husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.53,0:08:52.53,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,After all, a woman wants \Na man to protect her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.53,0:08:53.69,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Hey, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.69,0:08:54.96,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,If you keep it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.96,0:08:57.69,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I won't pay the rent or your wages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.16,0:09:02.54,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.54,0:09:04.00,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:06.80,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I'm useless, so it's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.70,0:09:10.81,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Sakagami-san, please don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.81,0:09:13.41,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,If your wife admits \Nto an illicit affair,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.41,0:09:15.15,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,we can sue her for compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.15,0:09:17.25,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,And the matter of being\N useless isn't that important,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.25,0:09:20.42,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,when it comes to the \Ndetermination of custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.42,0:09:23.46,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,What's important, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.46,0:09:27.61,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,In fact, there are three criteria \Nfor determining custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:43.84,Bengoshi-Vocab_Word,Caption in orange,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,0)}Criteria for determining custody
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.61,0:09:30.47,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Number one, quality of childcare.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.83,0:09:43.84,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition1,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,0)}(1) Quality of childcare.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.47,0:09:32.91,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Number two, mental and \Nphysical soundness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.46,0:09:43.84,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition2,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,0)}(2) Mental and physical soundness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.91,0:09:34.34,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,And number three,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.34,0:09:36.02,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,affection toward the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.50,0:09:43.84,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition1,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,0)}{\a3}(3) Affection toward the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.02,0:09:39.47,Bengoshi-Top,Kanae,0,0,0,,In other words, the advantage \Nof custody goes to the parent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.47,0:09:41.59,Bengoshi-Top,Kanae,0,0,0,,who does the best at childcare, \Nwho is of sound mind and health,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.59,0:09:43.84,Bengoshi-Top,Kanae,0,0,0,,and who is most affectionate \Ntoward their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:44.55,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.55,0:09:47.75,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The important thing in deciding custody
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.75,0:09:51.88,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,is which parent will ensure the children's happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:53.82,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,My children's happiness...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.82,0:09:55.57,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Sakagami-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.57,0:09:58.82,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Are you confident you can \Nmake your children happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.82,0:10:00.14,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.14,0:10:02.19,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I know can do better than\N my wife in that regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.19,0:10:03.41,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.41,0:10:06.57,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,In that case, you are \Nofficially my client.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.57,0:10:08.97,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Compensation. Custody. Child support.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.97,0:10:10.67,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Let's win them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.94,0:10:13.60,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I'm in your hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.60,0:10:17.40,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Now that it's official,\N let's start by gathering material.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.40,0:10:18.68,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Material?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:22.01,Bengoshi-Sakagami_Door_Sign,Plaque,0,0,0,,Sakagami
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:22.01,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Hakamada,0,0,0,,First, pertaining to the \Nquality of child care:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.01,0:10:26.34,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Hakamada,0,0,0,,please keep a detailed record \Nthat clearly shows who is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.68,0:10:26.08,Bengoshi-Credits_Izumi,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Takeshi's wife: \NSakagami Izumi
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.34,0:10:28.08,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Hakamada,0,0,0,,in charge of childcare.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.08,0:10:31.05,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,The kids want to go on \Na picnic this weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.95,0:10:32.46,Bengoshi-Calendar_15th,Calendar 15th,0,0,0,,Picnic
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.95,0:10:32.46,Bengoshi-Calendar_21st,Calendar 21st,0,0,0,,PTA meeting 15:00 ~
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.05,0:10:32.46,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'll be on a business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.46,0:10:35.01,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,How about on the parent\N visitation day the week after?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.01,0:10:37.81,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I can't take a weekday off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.81,0:10:39.26,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.26,0:10:40.70,Bengoshi-Class_Visit,Letter top,0,0,0,,Classroom Visit Information for Parents
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:43.80,Bengoshi-Class_Visit,Circle,0,0,0,,{\a9\b0\3c&H839790&}Only the father will attend{\b1}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.82,0:10:46.59,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Next, check on your health.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.17,0:10:49.34,Bengoshi-Health_Report,Diagnosis sheet top,0,0,0,,Detailed health evaluation report  \N{\b0}Areas of physical examination  Evaluation \NInternal examination: Good\N Exterior physical examination: Good \NColor perception examination: Good \NVisual examination: Good \NAuditory examination: Good \NBlood pressure examination: Good{\b1}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:50.25,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Hakamada,0,0,0,,It is important that there is both \Nphysical and mental soundness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.34,0:10:50.67,Bengoshi-Overall_Eval,Letter top,0,0,0,,{\a7}{\fs25\3c&HEAD9D5&}Health evaluation report
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.34,0:10:50.67,Bengoshi-Overall_Eval,Left top,0,0,0,,{\b0}Mr. Sakagami Takeshi{\b1}\N\N Overall evaluation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.64,0:10:52.64,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Hakamada,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.64,0:10:54.39,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,{\i1}Affection toward the children.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.64,0:10:54.84,Bengoshi-Credits,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Second son: \NSakagami Sorata
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.39,0:10:57.06,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Shower them with it as usual,\N without any reserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.06,0:10:58.31,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Hang in there, Sorata.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.48,0:11:00.02,Bengoshi-Credits_Daichi,Caption left,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Oldest son: \NSakagami Daichi
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.48,0:11:00.02,Bengoshi-Credits_Yuna,Caption right,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Oldest daughter: \NSakagami Yuna
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.31,0:11:00.02,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.77,0:11:02.11,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.11,0:11:03.84,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,You haven't left yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.84,0:11:06.16,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'm on my way home. I'll call you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.16,0:11:07.32,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:11.83,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.93,0:11:14.22,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.27,0:11:18.13,Bengoshi-Schedule,Form top,0,0,0,,Child Care Schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.53,0:11:21.50,Default,N,0,0,0,,Is there enough here \Nto convince the wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.50,0:11:22.89,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.89,0:11:23.31,Default,N,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.31,0:11:25.81,Default,N,0,0,0,,What's the point of this, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.81,0:11:29.44,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Usually, custody is determined \Nby mutual discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:31.31,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,But if they cannot reach an agreement,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.31,0:11:33.34,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,it goes to conciliation or trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.34,0:11:37.61,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,When it comes down to that, \Nappropriateness of custody
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.61,0:11:38.85,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,will be determined by a third party.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.85,0:11:42.89,Default,N,0,0,0,,So you're getting ready in \Ncase it goes to a conciliator.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.39,0:11:42.89,Bengoshi-Legal_Cases,BooKanae,0,0,0,,Newly Published Examples of Legal Cases
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.89,0:11:44.43,Bengoshi-Supreme_Court,Letter top,0,0,0,,Examples of supreme court hearings
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.89,0:11:45.08,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The truth is that when it \Ncomes to custody battles,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.08,0:11:48.24,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,the mother has a distinct advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.24,0:11:52.07,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The statistics say the mother is awarded custody \Napproximately 80% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.16,0:11:55.64,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition2,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,550)}Custody → Awarded to mother in 80% of cases
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.07,0:11:54.75,Bengoshi-Top,Kanae,0,0,0,,But, the mother is guilty \Nof an illicit affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:58.99,Bengoshi-Top,Kanae,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that fact give \NSakagami-san an advantage?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.99,0:12:03.91,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, illicit affairs have \Nlittle bearing on custody conciliation,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.91,0:12:07.45,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,because it can't be effectively argued \Nthat she can't care for her children,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.45,0:12:08.52,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,simply due to adulterous behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.52,0:12:10.42,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,So that's how it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.42,0:12:15.62,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,In that case, what more does \NSakagami-san need to receive custody?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.59,0:12:18.17,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.61,0:12:22.49,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Hakamada,0,0,0,,It would really help \Nif there's a neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.49,0:12:23.73,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Hakamada,0,0,0,,who assists him in childcare.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.73,0:12:24.45,Default,Misae,0,0,0,,Have a nice day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.93,0:12:27.33,Bengoshi-Credits_Misae,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Takeshi's big sister: \NHara Misae
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.45,0:12:27.03,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Thanks for babysitting today, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.03,0:12:28.57,Default,Misae,0,0,0,,We always have each others' backs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:31.05,Default,Misae,0,0,0,,Good luck at the job interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.67,0:12:35.04,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Auntie, when's lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.04,0:12:37.34,Default,Misae,0,0,0,,All right, all right, \Nit's omelettes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.31,0:12:41.02,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Okay, let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.93,0:12:42.79,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.79,0:12:44.88,Default,Yuna & Sorata,0,0,0,,It's the suspicious person!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:47.06,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Mister Suspicious Person, play with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.06,0:12:48.49,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You've got it wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:51.76,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,This man isn't a suspicious person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.76,0:12:52.83,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,He's a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.83,0:12:54.68,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,What's a lawyer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.08,0:12:58.80,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,A lawyer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.80,0:13:02.40,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,someone who helps those in trouble,\Nor who can't protect themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.40,0:13:04.56,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Wow, that's like a superhero of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.56,0:13:05.34,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.34,0:13:07.06,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,If anything troubles you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.06,0:13:09.54,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,you all can talk to Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.54,0:13:11.71,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,He will solve all your problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.71,0:13:14.01,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Really? Promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.65,0:13:16.16,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.15,0:13:23.23,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Pinky promise. If you lie, you have \Nto swallow a thousand needles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.23,0:13:24.82,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,It's sealed by our fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.82,0:13:26.39,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.39,0:13:27.44,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.14,0:13:29.71,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Hakamada-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.19,0:13:32.49,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,How was the job interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:36.67,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I got rejected. Again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.57,0:13:41.97,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,"Daruma-san... fell down!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.62,0:13:46.32,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Please cheer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.69,0:13:50.64,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The investigation is \Nmaking steady progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.64,0:13:52.94,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.94,0:13:56.40,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,At first I thought you \Nwere just suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.40,0:13:58.71,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,but you're actually an amazing person, \NHakamada sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.71,0:14:00.17,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.96,0:14:03.59,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,the battle has only just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.52,0:14:06.87,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The most crucial thing will be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.87,0:14:09.93,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,when you tell the children about the divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.67,0:14:14.34,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,When you tell them, you must not,\N under any circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.34,0:14:15.91,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,say anything disparaging about your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.73,0:14:17.77,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.77,0:14:19.31,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Though she is committing adultery,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.31,0:14:21.38,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,though she is not caring \Nfor the children,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.40,0:14:25.40,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Izumi-san is still \Ntheir mother, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.28,0:14:27.94,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,No matter how much animosity \Nlies between you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.94,0:14:31.89,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,the battle between husband and wife \Nshould never be revealed to the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.57,0:14:35.15,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.24,0:14:39.28,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,"Daruma-san fell down."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.28,0:14:42.43,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,You're it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.27,0:14:47.67,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Window_Sign,Letters,0,0,0,,Hakamada Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.81,0:14:47.67,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,I have the results of the \Nwife's background check.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.67,0:14:50.54,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Freelance investigator: \NUmemoto Kurumi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.67,0:14:51.54,Bengoshi-Top,Kurumi,0,0,0,,She's having a ball with her cheating partner,\N while calling it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.54,0:14:55.01,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,She comes home early in the morning \Nbecause she's been in hotels.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.01,0:14:57.35,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,What would the kids \Nthink if they found out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.35,0:15:00.08,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Looks like her daily excesses \Nare taking a toll on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:02.20,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Her health report isn't all that good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:02.82,Bengoshi-Health_Eval_Izumi,Letter top,0,0,0,,Health Examination Report
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:02.82,Bengoshi-Izumi_Name_Age,Next,0,0,0,,{\b0}Examinee name{\b1}\N Sakagami Izumi   {\fs18}Age 38 \N{\fs23}Grade \N{\fs30}D\N{\fs23}{\b0}Overall evaluation\N{\b1}Follow up essential{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.20,0:15:04.76,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,In contrast, there is no problem with \NTakeshi-san's childcare ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.76,0:15:09.79,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,state of health, \Nor affection toward his children.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.79,0:15:13.89,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,He's a failure as a man \Nbut a success as a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:17.32,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Based on this, Sakagami-san \Nmeets all the criteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.32,0:15:19.98,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Sensei, it looks like \Nhe could win custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.36,0:15:22.76,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,It's too soon to rejoice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.76,0:15:27.14,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,There is still one thing Sakagami-san \Nis missing to win custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.14,0:15:28.56,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.56,0:15:30.14,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Financial effectualness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.14,0:15:36.58,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,He must be able to provide for his children\N if he is to win custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:39.67,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,He needs to find work soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.67,0:15:41.45,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,so he can claim steady income.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.45,0:15:46.66,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,It's going to be quite tough \Nfor a man in his 40s to find work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.66,0:15:48.99,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.86,0:15:51.06,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:52.26,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.69,0:15:54.18,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I got a job. Finally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.18,0:15:57.20,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,They gave me an \Nunofficial letter of hire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.67,0:15:57.20,Bengoshi-Unofficial_Hire,Letter,0,0,0,,Mister Sakagami Takeshi \N{\b1}Informal notice of hire{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.20,0:15:58.30,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.30,0:16:00.01,Default,BotHakamada,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.01,0:16:03.28,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Looks like we're ready for battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.88,0:16:42.85,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,Horsey. Horsey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.65,0:16:43.30,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,Okay! Giddyap!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.19,0:16:48.01,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Hey, stop playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.01,0:16:49.27,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Go play in the other room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.27,0:16:50.88,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.88,0:16:52.02,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.02,0:16:53.57,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.27,0:17:06.22,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,This is from summer last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.22,0:17:09.44,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,We were still a close family, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.44,0:17:12.58,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.58,0:17:14.18,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,When are we going on the picnic?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.18,0:17:15.58,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You promised, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.58,0:17:17.92,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You said we're going on a family picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.92,0:17:18.62,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,I wanna go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.62,0:17:20.24,Default,Sorata,0,0,0,,I wanna go! I wanna go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.79,0:17:25.55,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.86,0:17:38.12,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Look after them, Daichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.12,0:17:39.92,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Yeah. We're going to the playground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.92,0:17:40.96,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.96,0:17:42.03,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.90,0:17:46.93,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,A lawyer? What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.97,0:17:48.14,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Business_Card,Biz card,0,0,0,,Hakamada Yukio, \NAttorney at Law
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.93,0:17:49.52,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Did you hire him using \Nthe money I earned?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.52,0:17:52.29,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Sakagami-san hasn't paid me anything yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.87,0:17:56.26,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I will get a portion of the \Ncompensation you will be paying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.26,0:17:57.59,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Compensation?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.55,0:18:00.67,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Compensation for illicit activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.83,0:18:06.37,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,This photo was taken \Non Saturday, February 15th.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.37,0:18:08.99,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun and children \Nwanted to go on a picnic,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.99,0:18:11.00,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,but you lied and said you \Nwere going on a business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.00,0:18:13.59,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Instead, you were having a secret \Ntryst with your illicit partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.59,0:18:15.95,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,This is from the day of \Nclassroom visitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.44,0:18:19.54,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,This is from the day of the PTA meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.54,0:18:23.70,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You have spent time \Nwith your illicit partner,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.70,0:18:25.96,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,under the pretext of working.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.96,0:18:27.64,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,And what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.64,0:18:31.23,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,That man means more to you \Nthan your children, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.23,0:18:32.96,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,So why do you want custody?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:34.64,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'm their mother. Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.64,0:18:37.00,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,"I'm their mother. Of course I do."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.00,0:18:37.96,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.96,0:18:41.41,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You're in a position of responsibility\N in your profession.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.41,0:18:44.37,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You will continue to work \Nafter you remarry, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.37,0:18:45.70,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Of course I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.70,0:18:49.20,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Who will look after the children, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.37,0:18:51.84,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.00,0:18:55.14,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I have definite plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.14,0:18:58.11,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,In case Sakagami-san gets custody,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.11,0:18:59.72,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Sakagami-san's sister, who recently
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.72,0:19:02.11,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,moved to the neighborhood, \Nwill help out with the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.92,0:19:06.55,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Do you have anyone who can help you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.21,0:19:08.95,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.43,0:19:11.15,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,You don't have anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.87,0:19:14.59,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,How do you plan on \Nraising your children?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.59,0:19:16.80,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'll hire a babysitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.08,0:19:21.43,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You won't raise your own children,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.43,0:19:23.74,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,but have someone else do it for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.68,0:19:27.11,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Will the kids be happy with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.41,0:19:30.53,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Who the hell do you think you are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.53,0:19:31.63,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,You're a total stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.63,0:19:33.87,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Stay out of our family's business!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.61,0:19:36.31,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I am not a total stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.69,0:19:39.78,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I am Daichi-kun's friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.59,0:19:42.05,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.05,0:19:43.22,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.28,0:20:04.11,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Daichi, hurry up and pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.11,0:20:06.10,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Yuna, Sonata, be quick about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.65,0:20:07.57,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.57,0:20:09.02,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.02,0:20:10.52,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Mama, what's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.52,0:20:12.66,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Let's go to your new Papa's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.66,0:20:13.68,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.68,0:20:15.81,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,New Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.81,0:20:18.31,Default,Sorata,0,0,0,,Is our Papa old?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.75,0:20:22.86,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Let's not stay with \Nthis no-good Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.86,0:20:26.05,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Let's live in a new house,\N with a new Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.05,0:20:28.04,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,You'll have lots of goodies to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.04,0:20:30.53,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,He'll buy you tons of stuff you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.53,0:20:31.36,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.14,0:20:37.82,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,I don't want a new Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.82,0:20:38.71,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,I'm not going!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.71,0:20:39.78,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.78,0:20:41.06,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,I'm not going, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.06,0:20:42.44,Default,Sonata,0,0,0,,I'm not going!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.44,0:20:44.91,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Stop being difficult, \Nand come with Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.91,0:20:45.53,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.53,0:20:46.99,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,I don't wanna go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.99,0:20:48.07,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,I'm not going!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.07,0:20:50.06,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Stop talking like that to the children!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.68,0:21:05.08,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'm coming back for all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.36,0:21:29.62,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,I got a call from Sakagami-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.62,0:21:32.97,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,The wife left the house\N without the kids, after our visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.97,0:21:35.60,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Isn't that really lucky for us, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.60,0:21:38.26,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Leaving the house and her kids behind
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.26,0:21:41.05,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,will put her at a disadvantage \Nin the custody battle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.50,0:21:45.29,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Yes, well, that's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.29,0:21:47.44,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.44,0:21:49.40,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,You look worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.40,0:21:53.78,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I may have made a huge mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.21,0:21:55.96,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.35,0:21:58.46,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Your clients are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.46,0:22:00.03,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.74,0:22:04.43,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Cute clients at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.43,0:22:06.06,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,I'll leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.06,0:22:07.76,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.76,0:22:09.60,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.47,0:22:16.30,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.47,0:22:16.90,Bengoshi-Pocket_Money,Envelopes,0,0,0,,Pocket Money
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.95,0:22:20.34,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.86,0:22:23.81,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Please don't let Papa \Nand Mama get divorced!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.67,0:22:25.64,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.64,0:22:26.85,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Mister,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.85,0:22:28.85,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,please make Papa and \NMama be friends again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.85,0:22:30.08,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.08,0:22:31.32,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.16,0:22:35.82,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,We want to live with Papa {\i1}and{\i0} Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.82,0:22:38.22,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,We don't want to be separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.43,0:22:51.58,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.43,0:22:54.88,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Your Papa and Mama will live separately...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.44,0:22:58.98,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,but your Mama will always be your Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.91,0:23:02.11,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You're a family, and that will never change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.80,0:23:07.91,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Your Papa, Mama, and I\N want you all to be happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.91,0:23:09.75,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,That's the most important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.75,0:23:10.72,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.30,0:23:15.79,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,If that's the most important thing, \Nwhy are they getting divorced?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.66,0:23:20.46,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,We want to be together \Nwith Papa and Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.30,0:23:26.48,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Isn't your job, Mister,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.48,0:23:27.92,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,to help people in trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.92,0:23:29.94,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Aren't you the superhero of justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.87,0:23:36.98,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You said you'd help \Nme if I'm in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.45,0:23:39.26,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.11,0:23:48.32,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You promised, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.83,0:24:00.27,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.27,0:24:01.07,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.27,0:24:05.19,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:07.93,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Come on. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.93,0:24:09.27,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.25,0:24:32.44,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.08,0:24:47.95,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble,Manga bubble,0,0,0,,Let's go to your \Nnew Papa's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.95,0:24:49.62,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble2,Manga bubble right,0,0,0,,New Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.95,0:24:49.62,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble3,Manga bubble left,0,0,0,,Is our Papa old?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.62,0:24:51.49,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble4,Manga bubble right,0,0,0,,I'm not going!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.62,0:24:51.49,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble2,Manga bubble middle,0,0,0,,{\3c&HB1C8D6&}I don't want \Na new papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.62,0:24:51.49,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble3,Manga bubble left,0,0,0,,{\3c&HA9BDCC&}I don't want it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.62,0:24:54.19,Bengoshi-Top,Misato,0,0,0,,Children are the victims \Nin custody battles, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.59,0:24:54.19,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Editor at Tokiwa Publishing: \NTabata Misato
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.19,0:24:56.12,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Misato-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.67,0:24:59.69,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,You're crying while reading my manga...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.89,0:25:02.26,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.56,0:25:07.23,Bengoshi-Credits,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Cafe waitress: \NMizutani Sara
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.66,0:25:07.43,Bengoshi-Top,Sara,0,0,0,,I see them. I feel them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.43,0:25:09.95,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,Spores spreading out into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.31,0:25:12.07,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,The cause of your tears is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.07,0:25:13.07,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,cedar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.07,0:25:15.53,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,Or perhaps cypress!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.53,0:25:17.05,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Do you have hay fever?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.05,0:25:20.04,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,It will get worse in spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.32,0:25:28.71,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,My handkerchief will need washing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.21,0:25:31.16,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.61,0:25:39.16,Default,All,0,0,0,,Delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.19,0:25:43.22,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,Which means... things aren't going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.22,0:25:47.17,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,He makes good bread \Nwhen he's distressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.73,0:25:49.19,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,I just heard,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.19,0:25:50.61,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Sakagami-san's wife has \Na legal representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.61,0:25:52.40,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,They called about the conciliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.26,0:25:54.64,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.36,0:26:02.07,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Sensei, are you worrying \Nabout the children?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.82,0:26:05.10,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Yes. You could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.10,0:26:07.10,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Sensei, you did nothing wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.10,0:26:10.09,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,I know they'll eventually understand.\N Daichi-kun, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.66,0:26:13.87,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,No. It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.88,0:26:20.04,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I told Sakagami-san that the children's feelings\N are of utmost importance, and yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.04,0:26:23.19,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,they heard about the divorce\N in the worst way possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.19,0:26:26.62,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,That's because the wife got \Nangry and left in a huff.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.62,0:26:28.68,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I'm the one who made his wife angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.24,0:26:31.75,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,It was my mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.46,0:26:43.08,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Yes, Hakamada Law Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.49,0:26:44.91,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Sakagami-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.55,0:26:46.83,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.83,0:26:48.74,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun and the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.43,0:26:52.63,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,They left quite a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.90,0:26:55.71,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Wood_Sign,Plaque,0,0,0,,Hakamada\NLaw Office
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.78,0:27:02.21,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Hakamada-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.22,0:27:04.15,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Sakagami-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.15,0:27:06.11,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,They're not at school or the playground.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.11,0:27:07.17,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,What about your sister's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.17,0:27:08.38,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Not there, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.38,0:27:10.16,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I bet it's my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.16,0:27:11.32,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,My wife kidnapped them!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.32,0:27:13.76,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Do you know where her new residence is?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.72,0:27:16.46,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I've got the address. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.46,0:27:18.28,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Sakagami-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.28,0:27:20.33,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The divorce is not yet final.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.26,0:27:30.14,Bengoshi-Vocab_Word,Caption orange,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,0)}If the divorce is not yet final
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.33,0:27:24.48,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,She can't be charged for kidnapping.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.13,0:27:30.14,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition2,Caption white,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,0)}{\a3}If the wife takes the children, \Nshe cannot be charged with kidnapping.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.48,0:27:26.16,Bengoshi-Top,Kanae,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.16,0:27:30.59,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Not only that, if your children's life\N with your wife stabilizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.59,0:27:33.66,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,there's a possibility that \Nyour wife will get custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.21,0:27:36.11,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.11,0:27:38.63,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Please, give the children back!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.63,0:27:40.95,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,You're stubborn. \NI told you, they're not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.95,0:27:41.58,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,You're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.58,0:27:42.76,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'm not lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.76,0:27:45.49,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,If you don't believe me, \Ngo look inside, everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.09,0:27:52.21,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,It's true that I approached them \Nand asked them to live with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.21,0:27:54.96,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,In front of that lawyer's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.96,0:27:56.00,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.37,0:27:59.37,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,They wouldn't come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.16,0:28:01.44,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.47,0:28:04.00,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.50,0:28:07.47,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Then, where could they be?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.47,0:28:08.74,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.74,0:28:10.88,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,It's your fault for neglecting them!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.88,0:28:12.37,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Don't make it my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.37,0:28:13.80,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,It's all your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.80,0:28:16.89,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,You'll be held responsible \Nif anything happens to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.89,0:28:18.58,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,This is no time for quarreling.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.58,0:28:20.16,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Let's split up and look for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.81,0:28:28.18,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.29,0:28:32.73,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.73,0:28:34.55,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.92,0:28:36.76,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Yuna-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.18,0:28:41.47,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Sorata-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.47,0:28:42.74,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.87,0:28:45.14,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Yuna!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.46,0:28:48.83,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Sorata!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.82,0:28:52.42,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,Brother, I'm cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.51,0:28:55.97,Default,Sorata,0,0,0,,Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.97,0:28:58.33,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,No way. We're never going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.33,0:29:01.21,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,Where's the picnic place?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.21,0:29:03.59,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,We'll never get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.57,0:29:05.83,Default,Sorata,0,0,0,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.07,0:29:11.54,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.54,0:29:13.40,Default,Sorata,0,0,0,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.40,0:29:14.51,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.79,0:29:34.19,Default,Kids,0,0,0,,Ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.19,0:29:35.59,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,Who are you calling a ghost?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.79,0:29:40.11,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,Hakamada-sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.11,0:29:42.66,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,I've got the kids. They're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.66,0:29:47.27,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,Thanks to Iron Spy Woman \NMarilyn, season 15, episode 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.07,0:29:46.37,Bengoshi-Spy_Marilyn,DVD box,0,0,0,,Iron Spy Woman\N{\fs25\3c&H1B191E&\c&H363839&}Marilyn
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.27,0:29:49.75,Default,Marilyn,0,0,0,,Finding missing persons \Nis easy as pie.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.75,0:29:50.34,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.34,0:29:55.80,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,99% of missing persons have left \Na clue behind in their homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.44,0:30:01.48,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Daichi, why did you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.97,0:30:05.79,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I won't know if you don't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.00,0:30:11.83,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,I think Daichi-kun \Nyearned for this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.83,0:30:14.40,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,where he and his family went together.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.35,0:30:17.67,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.59,0:30:20.84,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Daichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.11,0:30:24.69,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Please, don't give \Nyour Papa a hard time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.85,0:30:29.21,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You're the one giving us a hard time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.02,0:30:33.52,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,I want to live with Papa \Nand Mama. That's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.75,0:30:37.25,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Papa, you're stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.91,0:30:40.46,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.46,0:30:41.29,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.79,0:30:44.98,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,I hate you!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.98,0:30:46.03,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Daichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.03,0:30:47.64,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.95,0:30:50.66,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Mama told me about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.66,0:30:53.90,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You're not a superhero of justice!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.90,0:30:58.01,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,You're a villain that's splitting\N Mama and Papa apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.28,0:31:05.13,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,I'm not your friend anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.13,0:31:07.84,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Daichi, enough is enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.84,0:31:09.86,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Papa, Mama, and Mister,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.86,0:31:11.55,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,I hate you all!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.40,0:31:25.84,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,I don't believe you did \Nanything wrong, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.40,0:31:27.57,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.57,0:31:29.14,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,You're doing everything you can
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.14,0:31:30.70,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,to the best of your ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.70,0:31:33.07,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,for the sake of \NSakagami-san and the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.07,0:31:34.98,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,You've done nothing wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.49,0:31:39.35,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,No, he's not entirely incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.25,0:31:42.42,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,From the perspective \Nof the children,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.42,0:31:44.18,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I am a villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.91,0:31:51.27,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Because I'm helping their beloved \NPapa and Mama get a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.42,0:32:00.20,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,It's only natural that children\Nwill want to live as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.39,0:32:05.24,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I always felt that way \Nwhen I was a child, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.44,0:32:09.89,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,But, it was the wife's illicit activities
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.89,0:32:12.15,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,that broke the family apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.15,0:32:14.02,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,She doesn't participate in household duties,\N or caring for her children.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.02,0:32:16.62,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Instead she's out committing adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.62,0:32:18.68,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,How can the children be happy \Nliving with a mother like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.21,0:32:25.02,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Regardless, she's their \None and only mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.26,0:32:29.51,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,They want to live together as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.56,0:32:35.43,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Lawyers are powerless \Nat a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.90,0:32:55.15,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Sensei is so gloomy lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.15,0:32:57.02,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Tomorrow is the conciliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.02,0:32:59.62,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,I wonder if he's ready for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.47,0:33:02.07,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,The children running away
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.07,0:33:04.26,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,might reverberate loudly \Nat conciliation court.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.26,0:33:08.03,Default,Kurumi,0,0,0,,And if that happens,\N the mother will get custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.03,0:33:10.44,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,If that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.44,0:33:14.34,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,how will he pay the three \Nmonths worth of rent?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.20,0:33:18.67,Bengoshi-Court of Law,Plaque,0,0,0,,{\fad(1027,0)}Court of Law
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.43,0:33:20.16,Bengoshi-Top,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,We will now commence the \Nconciliation hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.67,0:33:22.61,Bengoshi-Family_Court,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Family Court: Conciliation Room
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.16,0:33:22.75,Bengoshi-Top,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,Both parties have their \Nrespective attorneys.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.75,0:33:26.05,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,Both parties have wished for them\N to be present at the discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.05,0:33:28.59,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,Hence, we have arranged \Nthe session accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.59,0:33:30.81,Default,Woman Conciliator,0,0,0,,According to the family conciliator,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.81,0:33:34.85,Default,Woman Conciliator,0,0,0,,it would be appropriate for the mother, \NIzumi-san, to get custody of her children.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.52,0:33:37.93,Bengoshi-Credits_Akiko,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Izumi's lawyer:\N Shoji Akiko
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.85,0:33:35.93,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,The other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.93,0:33:39.65,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,there was an incident wherein\N the children ran away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.65,0:33:43.21,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,The children were under \NTakeshi-san's supervision at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.21,0:33:45.87,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,If Takeshi-san were to get custody,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.87,0:33:48.89,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,something like that could\N very well happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.89,0:33:52.81,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I cannot rely on a person like that\N to watch over my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.81,0:33:55.31,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,And with regard to the \Nfinancial situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.31,0:33:58.92,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,pardon me for asking, but Takeshi-san, \Nwhat is your annual income?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.34,0:34:02.07,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I plan for it to be around\N three and a half million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.07,0:34:04.62,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,You recently found a job, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.62,0:34:05.50,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.50,0:34:07.49,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,At an electrical engineering company.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.49,0:34:10.32,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,I will work hard and get promoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.32,0:34:12.15,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Or get fired, again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.66,0:34:16.23,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,Izumi-san's annual income \Nis six million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.23,0:34:19.26,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,The partner she would remarry\N earns 12 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.26,0:34:21.91,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,That makes a total of 18 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.39,0:34:25.24,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,In terms of affording a good \Neducation for the children...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.24,0:34:26.97,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,they are nowhere lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.68,0:34:31.27,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Sensei, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.03,0:34:33.65,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,If I may.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.65,0:34:34.34,Default,Woman Conciliator,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.02,0:34:37.20,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Firstly, concerning \Nthe runaway incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.20,0:34:40.99,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Izumi-san is the cause of \Nthe children running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.99,0:34:43.93,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Izumi-san revealed the\N plan to divorce to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.93,0:34:46.51,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,and thereby hurt her \Nchildren's feelings deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.51,0:34:47.93,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.93,0:34:51.90,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The most careful one must \Nbe when divorcing...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.90,0:34:54.87,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,is when that fact is \Nrevealed to children.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.29,0:34:57.24,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,But Izumi-san lost \Ncontrol of her emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.24,0:34:59.10,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,She disparaged Takeshi-san \Nin front of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.63,0:35:02.01,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,and deeply hurt her children's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.01,0:35:04.12,Bengoshi-Flashback,Izumi,0,0,0,,Let's not stay here \Nwith this no-good Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.12,0:35:06.98,Bengoshi-Flashback,Izumi,0,0,0,,Let's live in a new house,\N with a new Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.98,0:35:09.04,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,She could very well have \Nsuch outbursts again,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.04,0:35:10.54,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,neglecting her children's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.54,0:35:12.72,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I merely spoke the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.72,0:35:14.79,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,There's no point in lying to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.59,0:35:19.61,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Next, with regard to the \Nfinancial situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.61,0:35:21.78,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Indeed, Izumi-san's new partner
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.78,0:35:24.50,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,is the president of an associate\N company, isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.62,0:35:28.19,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Have you changed your \Nmind about marrying him?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.19,0:35:29.90,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I have not.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.90,0:35:31.42,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.42,0:35:33.30,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,We have a problem, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.68,0:35:37.28,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,His annual income may \Nvery well be 12 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.28,0:35:41.28,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,But his company is in debt \Nfar beyond that amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.05,0:35:42.85,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.85,0:35:45.52,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,They've been in the red \Nfor several years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.52,0:35:47.35,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,They have been delinquent with taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.35,0:35:47.35,Bengoshi-Foreclosure_Warning,Letter title,0,0,0,,Federal Income Tax Delinquency: \NForeclosure Warning
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.35,0:35:48.79,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,They have unpaid salaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.49,0:35:48.79,Bengoshi-Unpaid_Wages,Letter title,0,0,0,,Bill for Unpaid Wages
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.79,0:35:50.96,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,They have been delinquent \Nin paying back loans.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.95,0:35:50.96,Bengoshi-Unpaid_Wages,Letter title,0,0,0,,Final Notice
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.96,0:35:54.31,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Thus, their bankruptcy \Nis only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.31,0:35:55.29,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.29,0:35:58.80,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Eventually, Izumi-san's income
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.80,0:36:01.63,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,will be redirected to paying back their debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.53,0:36:06.94,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You had said you would hire a babysitter\N to look after your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.94,0:36:08.89,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,That is looking rather difficult now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.89,0:36:12.58,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,How will you pay your attorney fees?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.21,0:36:14.21,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Also,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.21,0:36:17.37,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,your partner has a child \Nfrom his previous marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.37,0:36:19.26,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,His ex-wife has custody of the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.06,0:36:22.42,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Do you know why he gave her custody?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.04,0:36:26.49,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Because he knows it's better \Nfor the mother to have custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.49,0:36:27.98,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.36,0:36:31.01,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,It appears he doesn't \Nlike his child much.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.73,0:36:36.06,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,His violent actions toward his ex-wife and child\Nwere the cause of their divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.06,0:36:38.16,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The police became involved \Non multiple occasions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.04,0:36:45.31,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Will your children
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.31,0:36:47.71,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,be happy living with a person like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.20,0:37:05.13,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,I will now express my \Nopinion as conciliator.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.74,0:37:11.03,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,Gauging the overall situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.03,0:37:13.50,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,the custody of all three children
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.39,0:37:17.59,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,should go to the father, Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.59,0:37:19.38,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,Izumi-san, is this agreeable?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.17,0:37:21.86,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I cannot accept that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.86,0:37:23.87,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,If you cannot accept it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.87,0:37:25.55,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,we can dismiss the \Nconciliation as undetermined,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.55,0:37:28.65,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,and you can take it to court to \Nhave a judge make the decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.36,0:37:30.62,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,You can appeal it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.62,0:37:33.93,Default,Akiko,0,0,0,,but I doubt you'd get custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.41,0:37:40.06,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,It appears both parties \Nare in agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.06,0:37:42.45,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,I now declare the \Nconciliation as determined—
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.45,0:37:43.46,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,One moment please.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.19,0:37:45.30,Default,Man Conciliator,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.10,0:37:47.77,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I am sorry to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.77,0:37:52.58,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,but I think both Sakagami-san {\i1}and{\i0} \NIzumi-san are unfit to take on custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.05,0:37:54.54,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,Hakamada-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.18,0:38:00.99,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,If the two of you really \Ncare about your children,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.46,0:38:04.88,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,why did you destroy their happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.90,0:38:17.02,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,All you were concerned about\N was who would win custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.43,0:38:20.95,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Children are not your possessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.47,0:38:25.85,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,The children are innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.38,0:38:29.71,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Children always end up the victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.59,0:38:33.05,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,If you truly care about your children,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.02,0:38:37.03,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,then you must first ask their forgiveness,\N for having destroyed their happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.68,0:38:45.99,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You need to keep your heads bowed,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.81,0:38:48.53,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,until their wounds are healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.91,0:38:58.80,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,And you must wish for their happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.65,0:39:01.98,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,from the bottom of your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.83,0:39:11.91,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Isn't that where their happiness begins?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.91,0:39:26.25,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.94,0:39:29.25,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,You're a lawyer.\N What do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.84,0:39:31.17,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.75,0:39:52.38,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,We're going to be living \Napart from Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.01,0:39:54.46,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,It's Papa's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.16,0:39:58.49,Default,Takeshi,0,0,0,,This time it really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.49,0:40:02.59,Default,Sorata,0,0,0,,No! I don't want to \Nlive apart from Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.59,0:40:05.13,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,Why is Mama going away?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.13,0:40:08.14,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,I want Mama to live with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.36,0:40:12.44,Default,Yuna,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.88,0:40:25.45,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Outside_Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,Hakamada \NLaw Office
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.45,0:40:28.09,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,I'm so glad for Sakagami-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.09,0:40:29.72,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,He got custody and child support.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.72,0:40:33.24,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,But why did he withdraw \Nthe compensation fee?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.24,0:40:37.68,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,He must've taken Izumi-san's \Nfuture into consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.68,0:40:39.41,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,He's a pushover.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.41,0:40:42.41,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,If it were me, I'd mercilessly \Ncollect what I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.41,0:40:44.90,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,I'd chase them down to the pits of Hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.90,0:40:46.81,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Me too, to the pits of Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.81,0:40:48.90,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Oh! Rent comes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.90,0:40:50.54,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,My wages come first.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.54,0:40:51.88,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.88,0:40:53.68,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Your wages come last.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.68,0:40:54.50,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Never mind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.50,0:40:56.05,Default,Kanae,0,0,0,,Where is Hakamada-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.05,0:40:58.79,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Oh, come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.79,0:41:01.62,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,I bet he went into hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.62,0:41:05.46,Default,Yoshie,0,0,0,,Unforgiveable. I'll chase \Nhim to the pits of Hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.47,0:41:10.07,Default,Sorata,0,0,0,,Oh, it's Mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.07,0:41:10.83,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Stop, Sorata.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.83,0:41:13.57,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,That guy's not our friend any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.27,0:41:17.10,Default,Daichi,0,0,0,,Let's go play over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.50,0:41:19.82,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Daichi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.84,0:41:25.22,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.71,0:41:30.56,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,You're right about me, Daichi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.04,0:41:33.25,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I was a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.93,0:41:35.67,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I'm not cool at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.29,0:41:38.05,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I'm a no-good lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.41,0:41:43.78,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I couldn't keep my promise \Nwith my precious friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.48,0:41:47.60,Default,Hakamada,0,0,0,,I am truly sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.59,0:41:58.58,Bengoshi-Top,Daichi,0,0,0,,Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.11,0:42:07.45,Bengoshi-Top,Daichi,0,0,0,,I already knew you're no superhero.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.89,0:42:10.20,Bengoshi-Top,Yuna,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.20,0:42:11.52,Bengoshi-Top,Sorata,0,0,0,,I knew it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.52,0:42:13.94,Bengoshi-Top,Daichi,0,0,0,,I never thought you were cool, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.94,0:42:14.93,Bengoshi-Top,Yuna,0,0,0,,I never thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.93,0:42:16.30,Bengoshi-Top,Sorata,0,0,0,,I never thought so!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.30,0:42:17.60,Bengoshi-Top,Daichi,0,0,0,,One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.50,0:42:22.05,Bengoshi-Top,Daichi,0,0,0,,But we'll play with you anyway. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.05,0:42:22.77,Bengoshi-Top,Daichi,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.18,0:42:27.01,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.64,0:42:28.97,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.42,0:42:33.34,Bengoshi-Top,Daichi,0,0,0,,You better run!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.34,0:42:35.08,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.65,0:42:39.03,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.00,0:42:42.38,Bengoshi-Top,Hakamada,0,0,0,,Wait!
